DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260720T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260720T193000
SUMMARY:🍽️ Dinner: Ground Beef Tacos
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Ground Beef Tacos\nServings: 4\nPrep: 10 min | Cook: 15 min | Total: 25 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 1 lb ground beef\n• 8 small flour tortillas\n• 1 tbsp chili powder\n• 1 tsp cumin\n• 0.5 tsp garlic powder\n• 0.5 tsp onion powder\n• 0.25 cup water\n• 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n• 1 cup lettuce\n• 2 tomato\n• 0.5 cup sour cream\n• 1 lime\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Brown ground beef in a skillet over medium-high heat, breaking it up as it cooks.\n2. Drain excess fat. Add chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, and water.\n3. Simmer 5 minutes until sauce thickens.\n4. Warm tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave.\n5. Assemble tacos with beef, cheese, lettuce, diced tomato, sour cream, and lime juice.\n\nTip: Works great with ground turkey too. Add jalapeño for heat.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mealplan-20260721-breakfast-4@mealplanner
DTSTAMP:20260724T121436Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260721T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260721T090000
SUMMARY:🍳 Breakfast: Overnight Oats
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Overnight Oats\nServings: 2\nPrep: 5 min | Total: 5 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 1 cup rolled oats\n• 1 cup milk\n• 0.5 cup greek yogurt\n• 2 tbsp honey\n• 0.5 cup blueberries\n• 2 tbsp chia seeds\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Combine oats, milk, yogurt, honey, and chia seeds in a jar or container.\n2. Stir well, cover, and refrigerate overnight (or at least 4 hours).\n3. Top with blueberries before serving. Eat cold or microwave 1-2 min.\n\nTip: Swap blueberries for banana, strawberries, or any fruit. Add peanut butter for extra protein.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
